{
  "texts": [
    "Constrained decoding of language models by Shin et al. [21] demonstrated the paraphrasing of user utterances into a regulated sublanguage for enhanced semantic parsing.Recent contributions by Norouzi et al.",
    "[32] showcased transformer-based seq2seq models competing with or outperforming models specifically designed for code generation.",
    "Beau and Crabbé [34] proposed an encoder-decoder model using BERT as an encoder and a grammar-based decoder, achieving a BLEU score of 34.2 on the CoNaLa dataset.",
    "Semantic parsing based techniquesSemantic parsing, a subset of natural language processing, involves translating natural language utterances into machine-understandable logical forms.",
    "The overarching aim is to extract precise meaning, enabling machines to comprehend and execute these utterances."
  ]
}